-- China President Hu Urges Energy Conservation, Trade Cooperation With U.K.
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-10T05:34:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-10/china-president-hu-urges-energy-conservation-trade-cooperation-with-u-k-.html
Chinese President Hu Jintao urged
cooperations with the U.K. in the alternative energy, new
materials, energy conservation and high-end manufacturing
industries during a meeting with U.K. Prime Minister David
Cameron today, according to a statement posted on the Ministry
of Foreign Affairs’s website.  Hu also called for the U.K.’s cooperation in fighting trade
protectionism, the statement said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
